The Company starts its services with the only planes speciﬁcally de- signed for comfortable, low-fare ﬂights, the giant Super—6 Clippers with accommodations for 82 passengers. Pan American will be providing bet- ter than two a day service each way across the Atlantic with Super-6s di- rect to eight cities in Europe and also better than two a day on the deluxe “President” double—deck Clipper serv— ice. The round trip fare to London on the tourist service, for example, is $486 compared with $711 on the de- luxe service.
